$ CorFlags.exe

`CorFlags.exe` allows to set or clear the following bits/flags from the *CorFlags section* of the header of a → Windows/development/Portable-Executable/EXE[portable executable] image:
  • 32BITREQUIRED
  • 32BITPREFERRED
  • ILONLY

Additionally, it allows to change the CLR header version from 2.0 to 2.5 or vice versa.

`CorFlags.exe` is installed with → Windows/development/Visual-Studio and located under
→ Windows/dirs/Program-Files-x86/Microsoft-SDKs/Windows/version/bin/NETFX-version-Tools[`%WindowsSDK_ExecutablePath_x86%`].
